{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"77f5e0a5-064a-4133-8819-cf2ec79d1b3c","content":"Neither — use **`dotnet watch`**.\n\n- `dotnet watch test` — re-runs tests automatically when files change.\n- `dotnet watch run` — re-runs the app on file changes.\n\n`dotnet test` and `dotnet run` are one-shot commands; they don't monitor for changes. The `watch` verb is what enables hot reload / live reloading.\n\nSince your project is a test project, you'd want:\n\n```bash\ndotnet watch test\n```\n\nThis will watch your source files and re-execute tests whenever you save a change.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b53ccc04-e767-47b3-abf7-7363949a507c","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about hot reload in .NET - specifically whether to use `dotnet test` or `dotnet run` to benefit from hot reload. Let me look at the project files to understand the context.","outputTokens":191,"requestId":"0427:28DE61:1A0AC99:1D87888:69E82426"},"id":"18cbcf51-673b-471d-92e4-d4664a07ae78","timestamp":"2026-04-22T01:28:13.785Z","parentId":"f7a04372-b95b-4bfb-a19b-07e06a43a3d1"}
